{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App\/GettingStarted"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to build and run the Swift Package Registry Service."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Github-Personal-Access-Token","level":2,"text":"Github Personal Access Token"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Many methods of the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.github.com\/en\/rest?apiVersion=2022-11-28","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is accessible without authentication.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.github.com\/en\/rest\/using-the-rest-api\/rate-limits-for-the-rest-api?apiVersion=2022-11-28","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are much lower. Therefore, it is advisable to provide the service with a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/docs.github.com\/en\/authentication\/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure\/managing-your-personal-access-tokens","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to authenticate with the Github API.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Building and running migrations","anchor":"Building-and-running-migrations","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Check out the repo and do an initial build using the ","type":"text"},{"code":"swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" command line:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["git clone https:\/\/github.com\/CrowdStrike\/swift-package-registry-service.git","cd swift-package-registry-service","swift build"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let’s set up the database which is used for parts of the disk cache:"}]},{"code":["swift run App migrate"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should see something like:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["$ swift run App migrate","...","Build of product 'App' complete! (92.19s)","Migrate Command: Prepare","The following migration(s) will be prepared:","+ App.CreateRepositories on <default>","Would you like to continue?","y\/n> "],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Type ‘y’ and then hit Return. Then you should see:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["y\/n> y ","[ INFO ] [Migrator] Starting prepare [database-id: sqlite, migration: App.CreateRepositories]","[ INFO ] [Migrator] Finished prepare [database-id: sqlite, migration: App.CreateRepositories]","Migration successful"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Now you should see a directory created called ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".sprsCache"},{"type":"text","text":" and a "},{"code":"db.sqlite","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" file inside that directory:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["$ ls -l .sprsCache","total 48","-rw-r--r--  1 <your-username>  staff  24576 Mar 24 14:27 db.sqlite"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"text":"Running the service from the command line","type":"heading","anchor":"Running-the-service-from-the-command-line"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Now that you have created the disk cache database, then you are now ready to run the service:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["$ export GITHUB_API_TOKEN=\"<your-Github-PAT>\"","$ swift run App serve","Building for debugging...","...","Build of product 'App' complete! (25.07s)","[ NOTICE ] Server started on http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Testing-the-service-using-curl","text":"Testing the service using curl","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you point Swift Package Manager 